<DOC><DOCNO> AP880412-0042 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-12-88 0239EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Salvador-Recount     04-12 0195</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Salvador-Recount,0199</SECOND><HEAD>Arena Asks Vote Recount In Eastern El Salvador</HEAD><DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The rightist party that wonlast month's legislative elections has filed a request for a voterecount in La Union, the country's easternmost province.   The Central Elections Council last week announced that therightist Nationalist Republican Alliance, or Arena, had won 30 of60 seats in the unicameral legislature in nationwide elections heldMarch 20.   All 60 seats in the Assembly were decided, as well as municipalauthorities in 262 towns and cities. The council said the incumbentChristian Democratic Party won 23 Assembly seats and the NationalConciliation Party won seven.   Arena, which won 178 of the municipalities, claimed it alsogained an outright majority in the Assembly. It charged theChristian Democrats with trying to ``steal'' a deputy in La Union.   Preliminary results from the province indicated Arena had takentwo of three deputy seats. But final results released by thecouncil gave only one to Arena and two to the Christian Democrats.   Arena filed its request for a recount on Monday. The council hasuntil Wednesday to decided whether to grant or reject the request.</TEXT></DOC>